{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "01", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "37", "S": "53"}}, "news": [{"title": "Tier-II city homebuyers in Karnataka drive up demand for duplex apartments", "para": "Duplex apartments are gaining popularity in North Karnataka cities like Hubballi and Belagavi. This trend, driven by buyer demand, offers spacious living and privacy. Developers are responding to this shift, with a notable increase in duplex and penthouse constructions. Buyers are opting for these homes for safety, shared maintenance, and customized interiors, redefining urban living in these growing cities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/growing-demand-for-duplex-apartments-in-karnatakas-tier-ii-cities/129939806?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26838/129939806.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Bombay HC orders Nagpur-based builder to deposit \u20b941 lakh for demolition costs", "para": "The Bombay High Court has ordered builder N Kumar to pay over \u20b941 lakh for demolishing illegal structures. The court mandated the deposit within two weeks. Demolition work at Poonam Chambers and Poonam Tower is underway. The Nagpur Municipal Corporation expects to complete the demolition by April 10.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bombay-high-court-orders-builder-to-pay-41-lakh-for-illegal-demolitions/129939569?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26322/129939569.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Property buyers in Bhopal rush to finish registrations before new rate hike", "para": "Bhopal's registration offices saw an unprecedented surge on March 31, with over 1,000 property deals finalized before significant stamp duty hikes took effect.  Buyers scrambled to complete transactions, with some securing slots in the early morning.  The increased rates, ranging from 50% to over 180% in various locations, will impact property purchases from April 1.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bhopal-property-buyers-rush-to-beat-stamp-duty-hike-before-april-1/129939494?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-28250/129939494.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}